==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumfuse
<hw>Cir`cum*fuse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumfusus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>circumfundere</ets> to pour
around; <ets>circum + fundere</ets> to pour.]</ety> <def>To pour round;
to spread round.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His army <qex>circumfused</qex> on either wing.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumfusile</ent>⟦br⟧
